--open terminal and  instal json-server 


  --> npm install -g json-server 

create a new angular project 

--> ng new httpdemo --no-standalone

  open terminal 

  json-server --watch db.json

  if it gives an error that is db.json not found ... 
  -> open your angular project in explorer paste the db.json file provided in day 65 repo 

copy and paste the db.json (downloaded) in httpdemo project that we just now created in the above cmds 


  json-server --watch db.json

  your restapi will start on port 3000 

  htpp://localhost:3000/cars


--. download and install postman to test the fake rest api created using json-server

open post man the test get request choose method get and type this url 

--> get all cars 
http://localhost:3000/cars  

--> get car by id
http://localhost:3000/cars/1


-->get cars by color
http://localhost:3000/cars?color=white



make a post request now in another postman tab 

